description:
The Railway Club Hotel/Owens restaurant has remained one of the busiest dining rooms in Melbourne for over ten years. Its atmosphere and ambiance has stood the test of time. No pretence, just true Port Melbourne style.

You can pick your own meat from our display fridge and see it cooked to perfection at our open kitchen. With such a commanding range of cuts and sizes we never disappoint.

But it’s not just all about the steaks. We are also famous for our seafood and expansive selection of specials. Try our chef’s-own Cevapcici skinless sausages with olive tapenade, or our whole grilled 500g flounder.

Our chefs pride themselves on the quality and freshness of their selected produce. All food is made on the premises — we even make are own ice creams and desserts.

We also have an expansive wine-list, with a huge range of premium reds. Our own cellared wines and tempting reserve wine-list are perfect for any special occasion.

about: Hunky Dory was establish in 2004 as a family business with a vision to offering healthier seafood options along with the more traditional fish and chips.
description:
A family of fishermen since 1927.

Inspired by almost 90 years of fishing on the Greek Islands, Hunky Dory was establish in 2004 as a family business with a vision to offering healthier seafood options along with the more traditional fish and chips. Whether it’s a delicious grilled fillet of Salmon or Whiting, Greek or spinach salad and a healthy serve of brown rice, there’s something for everyone. Traditionally fish and chips have been a take away food, but we wanted to create a comfortable and casual setting where customers could dine in and enjoy a glass or wine or a beer with their food.

Our aim is to be the best at what we do. We take pride in preparing and cooking fresh, tasty and healthy meals made to order. Our seafood is delivered from the markets daily and filleted on site to ensure you get the best quality. Our mouth-watering seafood is delicious and tasty incorporating unique marinades and sauces that will keep you coming back. Our menu provides many healthy options such as simply grilled fish and wholesome salads to create a perfectly balanced meal.

At Hunky Dory, you’re part of the family.

Greg Robotis, Managing Director & Founder
name: Hunky Dory Fish & Chips

about:
Cafe during the day & American BBQ and Burgers by night.

Slow smoked meats include pork and beef ribs, brisket, chicken & much more.

Now with over 12 different burgers.
description:
Third Wave has become a religious experience on the Melbourne restaurant scene. Since opening in 2010, we have cemented a reputation as a great neighborhood cafe with a loyal breakfast and lunch crowd. People come from far and wide to enjoy our exceptional coffees and vast breakfast & lunch menu. Then by night, we transform into a bustling BBQ joint, inspired by the classic American smoke houses of the deep south. Today we are proud to be recognised as one of the best American BBQ experiences you'll have outside of the US.

How it began
Inga is the passionate owner of Third Wave Cafe, a lady with a fierce drive for delivering a quality product, which spills into every area of the business, from grass fed locally sourced meat to perfectly textured milk in your coffee from 5 Senses beans. Its been Inga’s dream to own and operate a café. So after nagging her husband for about a decade, the dream finally came true.

We like to think we have mastered the art of slow smoking, especially using our custom built smoker, named Brutus. Our American BBQ meats are melt-in-your mouth, fall-off-the-bone delicious. The house made BBQ sauces are so good that some customers want to drink them.

Uniquely, you can have our amazing menu delivered to your home. We deliver up to 10km from Port Melbourne, 7 days a week. Order online on our website or call 96762399. Our delivery service extends to a full catering service where the whole menu can be ordered for your private functions delivered to most areas of Melbourne.
name: Third Wave Cafe

about:
Traditional french baking since 1825

Port Melbourne - 84 Bay St - 9646 9555
Bentleigh - 412 Centre Rd - 9557 7110
description:
My family history begins before 1825. At that time my great-grandfather was baking homemade bread for himself and his neighbours. His bread was in such demand that he decided to start what would become his legacy.

In starting the first boulangerie, every generation has continued the tradition; uncles and cousins, males and females have chosen to become bakers or pastry chefs.

I think of what my family has created, in respect of traditional bread. At no time has what I am doing been an obligation, it was simply love for the earth – the simple elements that combined, infuse you with those flavours.

Now I have the privilege to write another page in our history, and to share my family’s passion with all of you.

David, 5th generation
name: Noisette

about: Dog friendly whisky and cocktail lounge! Our bar is your escape den, a cubby hole, a tree house …only with gin, whisky, cocktails and much much more!
description:
The Tipsy Cow is a den for grown-ups.

A place for everyone to gather, and leave behind the stresses of ‘real’ life at the door. Where you can hang out with your friends, your family, or by yourself.

Melt into our comfy setting and allow the tensions of your day to melt away. 

​

When we were kids and we made castles in our bedrooms with cushions, remember how much fun it was?

How nothing in the world could touch us for as long as our castle walls protected us from the outside world.

It was cozy, comfortable, welcoming, and the possibilities were endless.

We were Warriors, and Kings and Queens!!! 

This is the type of space we have created here, and want to share.

​

Everyone is on a journey, and every single day we give the world our best. So when a traveler is tired and needs some rest and recuperation, we are there.

There is nothing in this world that a warm welcoming space, some good wholesome food, garnished with anecdotes of your nostalgia, and the sweet embrace of an elixir cannot fix. 

​

Welcome to The Tipsy Cow, your den, your hideaway, your luxury cushion castle.

about: Eire artisan Pies are hand crafted chunky style, rustic pies made from the freshest ingredients.
description: When Eire first opened, it was a new concept for the suburb of Clapham. Eire Café had taken up space where there once was a deli or a take way food shop.  Tradies were the main clientele and they would stop there for their Mrs Macs pie.  From the get go, Stephen had decided that he would only sell what he made.  This was putting out some of the regular customers that used to drop in before Eire Café. One day, a cranky tradesman stopped in and gave Stephen a serve about not stocking pies. Stephen told him to come back the next day and he would have a pie for him. In that first week of making pies, he made 6 and sold 6 then he made 10 and then 50 and so on .....  That tradesman still comes in to this day.
name: Eire Pies
